  "body": "Fixes #33486\r\n\r\nThe issue in #33486 was caused by the use of `GetFullPathName` on Windows in the `absrealpath` C function.\r\n\r\n`GetFullPathName` does not always return a UTF-8 encoded path.\r\n`absrealpath` is used to set the paths in `jl_options`.\r\nSo if Julia is run from a non-ASCII directory with a non-UTF-8 locale, the paths in `jl_options` are broken.\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes this by using `uv_fs_realpath` and `uv_cwd` from libuv, which handles conversion of Windows paths to WTF-8.",
